                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="andycapp_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">the main character in a British <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/comic-strip" title="comic strip definition"><span class="ndv">comic strip</span></a> created by Reg Smythe (1917-1998) which first appeared in the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-daily-mirror#the_daily_mirror_topg_1" title="Daily Mirror definition"><span class="ndv">Daily Mirror</span></a> newspaper in 1957. The cartoon also appeared in newspapers in the US. <span class="dh">Andy Capp</span> drinks a lot, is very lazy, and is unfair to his wife Flo. He always wears a <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/flat-cap" title="flat cap definition"><span class="ndv">flat cap</span></a> and has a cigarette hanging from his mouth.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
